description: Vince graduated from Central Michigan University and has done marketing and design work for a multitude of companies from big to small. He has been designing websites since 1994, and has utilized that expertise to solve his clients' internet crises. Past design and marketing customers include Ford, Maytag and Auto Trader, while he also did design concepts for Kraft, Dr. Pepper, Absopure and Auto Trader. Vince was the head designer for Michigan Hockey magazine before moving up to designing Mousetraps.
name: Vincent Cracchiolo

description: Freelance illustrator and conceptual designer, Owner of Caldwellink.com, and Graduate of the Joe Kubert School. With over 150 patents and 15 years of experience in visual art media and design. Specializing in digital painting, conceptual design, and sequential storytelling. Chris helps companies like Ford, Pepsi, Sony, Kraft, Dr. Pepper, Chevron, and Proctor & Gamble, enhance their brand and make their products stand out from the competition.
name: Chris Caldwell
